ad.title: Haven't experienced yet in Paris
ad.content:
My name is Didith. I am 46 years old and I have 10 years experienced in baby sitting from 0 month old until 11 years old. 
These are the responsibilities I had been when I took care of a new born baby. First, feeding-Newborns eat every 2-3 hours, whether breastfed or formula-fed. Follow the parent's instructions for feeding schedules. Ensure bottles are properly sterilized if using formula. Second, burping-
Always burp the baby after feeding by gently patting their back while holding them upright. Next, Diaper Changes-Newborns need frequent diaper changes (every 2-3 hours or as needed). Be prepared for wet and soiled diapers. Keep diapers, wipes, and diaper cream nearby. Fourth, Sleep-Newborns sleep a lot‚Äî16-18 hours a day in short intervals. Always place the baby on their back in a safe sleep environment. Soothing, Swaddling, gentle rocking, or using a pacifier can help soothe a fussy baby. Soft white noise or calming music can also help. Hygiene, Wash your hands before handling the baby. Avoid exposing the baby to sick individuals. Monitor Crying, Newborns cry for several reasons: hunger, diaper changes, discomfort, or needing to be held. Try to address their needs calmly and patiently. Safety
Never leave a newborn unattended, especially on high surfaces. Support the baby's head and neck at all times. Lastly and very important, Parent Communication- Keep a log of feedings, diaper changes, and any concerns to report to the parents. Follow any specific instructions the parents provide.

Here are my  responsibilities when I took care of a toddler until 11 years old. I assist them with bathing, dressing, and potty training during toddler years. I Ensure the child maintains personal hygiene as they grow. I keep checking all the activities and schedule.
